leads.lead_text: Flowers with 6 or 7 fertile anthers of differing sizes, sometimes beaked; pods cylindric
Flowers with 10 fertile anthers, subequal, truncate; pods compressed
Fertile stamens 6; gland at base of petiole, flat
Fertile stamens 7; glands between lowest 2–4 pairs of leaflets, erect
